      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely! Concrete has excellent compressive strength, meaning it can handle large forces trying to crush it. However, it isn't very good at handling tension or stretching forces. Steel rebar is added to concrete because it has high tensile strength, complementing the concrete's compressive strength. This combination of materials helps the foundation resist bending and cracking under loads, ensuring stability and strength in the structure built on it.",
